						h2.section-title The Client
						p American Express creates tools for their credit business targeted for consumer and corporate clients.
					.page-section
						h2.section-title The Problem
						p American Express had been providing an outdated expense reporting tool to corporate customers. Over time, the tool had become bloated with outdated functionality and confusing user interactions. 
					.page-section
						h2.section-title The Solution
						p Pivotal and American Express developed a modern version of their corporate expense reporting tool with input from their large customer base around the world. 
					.page-section
						h2.section-title My Role
						p As lead product designer from Pivotal, I worked collaboratively with the client, engineers, and product manager. I conducted research/experiments, prioritized solutions, wireframed/prototyped and created live styleguides. I also helped American Express hire and ramp-up a new product designer that would be dedicated to this project.
