						h2.section-title Continued Iteration
						p After we had a grasp on the base functionality for the new app I focused on creating a componentized design system that could be expanded as we built out additional features. We also incorporated weekly usability sessions in order to smooth out major workflows allowing people to work quickly.
				.col-md-6
					.page-section
						p Design responsibilities included:
						ul.default-ul
							li Creating a live styleguide that could be referenced in order to keep consistency across different development tracks.
							li Tracking and sharing progress of design and user validation with wider group of stakeholders.
							li Prototyping and iterating on upcoming features in our coded prototype.
							li Helping American Express hire a full-time product designer to take over long-term responsibilities for the app.
				.col-md-6
					.page-section
						p The app has now launched to a set of four beta customers. We also successfully hired and ramped-up a full-time product designer who has taken on design leadership and responsibilities for the app. The team continues to roll out additional features based on customer feedback and identified business opportunities.
